The '''Ship-Shore-Ship Buffer''' (SSSB) is a [[real-time data]] link buffer system supporting data exchange between naval forces, including airborne assets, and their associated air defence ground environment units.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://npc.ncia.nato.int/Pages/Ship-Shore-Ship-Buffer-(SSSB).aspx|title=Ship-Shore-Ship Buffer (SSSB)|publisher=NATO}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Ince|first=A. N. |year=1992|chapter=Current Nato Communications Planning (SATCOM and the Nato C3 Architecture)|title=Digital Satellite Communications Systems and Technologies|pages=9-30|publisher=Springer|location=Boston, MA}}</ref>

